`apps/user-manager-api` is an Express backend integrating SuperTokens. Package manager: **pnpm** (Node workspace). Serves on `:3001`.

This is the **shared SSO hub** for the monorepo (Flutter timemanager, React user-manager-web, and future apps).

Key files:

- `index.ts` — entrypoint: initializes SuperTokens, CORS (React `:3000` + Flutter localhost origins), mounts SuperTokens middleware. Endpoints: `/hello` (public), `/sessioninfo` (session-protected), `/tenants` (multitenant list), `/auth/*` (SuperTokens).
- `config.ts` — SuperTokens backend config (`connectionURI`, `appInfo`, `recipeList`). Session recipe accepts cookie (React) and header (Flutter) via `st-auth-mode`; access-token payload includes `email` for GraphQL user mapping. JWKS at `/auth/jwt/jwks.json`.

Auth flow: clients never call the SuperTokens Core directly — they call this backend, which calls the Core. SuperTokens auto-handles requests under `${apiDomain}/auth`.

Commands: `nx serve user-manager-api` (continuous; also started by `nx serve timemanager`), `nx build user-manager-api` (`tsc`), `nx lint user-manager-api`.
